If love was a gamble, then I'd be a gambler.
If love was a poison that rips up my heart...
Sending piercing pain and joy into my veins...
Then, girl, I'll be happy to take that shot for you.
If love let me fall deeply for you;
Let me snuggle you with sweet embrace;
Let us make music and melodies with our moans of ecstasy,
Then, my God, let me fall in love.
Let me fall deeply in an all-consuming love;
My soul, my mind, and my body are yours.
Days, hours, minutes, seconds--I will be thinking of you;
Of your soft lips gliding down my neck and my hands gently teasing your torso;
Or the countless of times you whisper my name, and I yours;
Or the endless silent conversations that we have where no one spoke, but it was more than enough...

Me: Asian, lesbian, hopeless romantic, trustworthy, loyal, ambitious, great cook, great cuddler, tech-savvy, gamer, amateur guitarist, amateur poet, loves the outdoors, loves animals, wants to be a butterfly one day (ask me about it), wants a family (be it with kids or adopted animals), prefers tea over coffee. 

You: FEMALE, SINGLE, 23-28 years old, Caucasian/Asian, confident, independent, health conscious, down to earth, the girl next door, an adventurer, shy but also has a crazy side that yearns to be free, has an idea of what you want to do in life (doesn't have to be set in stone), wants more than a one night stand, can hold a conversation, am interested in me and will put in the effort to get to know me (I will do the same).

Respond to email with: the title of your favorite Movie/TV Series attached with a picture of you. Keep it PG.

[ABSOLUTELY NO MEN/COUPLES/DRUGS/STDs]

Buongiorno, 

Generally, I am interested in the person, not in their astrology, however, for this, I am solely relying on astrology to sharply narrow my options; particularly the possibility of being hurt due to some fundamental astro incompatibilities. Granted there are many things in life, other than astrological compatibility, that count for something, in relationships, however, who I am looking for is special. The relationship I am opening myself to be a part of is also special, and somewhat date specific. After decades of attracting the wrong type of women, I finally got into astrology, clearly saw why, and clearly saw the workaround. This is part of the workaround; only partnering with a woman whose astro profile is like a key to my lock, and vice verse. It promises to be a very loving, sensitive, passionate, and dynamic relationship! 

Me: Basically, I am a highly sensitive, primarily spiritually-minded, creative, dreamer-type, gentle, caring, intense, brainy, fun, funny, deep, multicultural, multi-ethnic transwoman of color. I am a very youthful older woman, in my late 50's. [I am inherently outgoing, but I have been deeply harmed, and I live with clinical depression, frequently fearing social interaction, to the extent of preferring to live in the shadows; the image is a good representation of that.] I am (an Internet-based) professional, and I do a lot of business in Asia, and New Zealand, so I work at night, and need a nocturnal-oriented partner. My most consistent demeanor is kind, gentle, mysterious, and somehow, not of this world.

I avoid opening myself up to intimate relationships with white, and Jewish women; based on too many adverse experiences with them, as groups. Otherwise, ethnicity is irrelevant; although I really DO have a heart thing for Native American, Japanese, (Western) French and Persian women. 

I have weak knees for tall women, i.e. 5'10"+. I tend to regard short women only as friends. Otherwise, my description of you generally applies to me too; older women are more substance-oriented, then sensation-oriented--one of the best reasons for younger women to be with us--so pardon the pun, the list is substantial.

You: 
[Most Important!] Your primary motivation in life is to attain the highest degree of Holiness that you may, and you live for Love's sake, more than any other reason--and that includes having a dedicated yoga, meditation, and spiritual practice; #
you are very sure, and solid in your own "positions" , and are not threatened by positions of others that may be inconsistent with yours;
you are serious, but not too serious to be unable to laugh at yourself;
you know how to get in touch with, and talk about your feelings, rather than relying on emotional outbursts to let your partner know something is not copacetic; 
you although assertive, you are not into being dominant; 
you live creatively, and don't need to take the same route anywhere twice in a row; 
you would rather cuddle, and listen to fantasy stories on audiobook, than go to any sports event--I don't EVER wish to hear more than a few seconds of sports broadcasts when we're together; 
you are a professional, if not typically, then creatively, or both; 
you have no STDs, dogs, psychotic ex-girlfriends, or queer-hatin' family; 
you are very, very affectionate, with words, and touch, [publicly is not necessary]; 
you are physically attractive, thin, (and into being thin), and good looking, with zero conceit, or narcissism; 
you are romantically inclined toward well-educated, spiritually-minded, women of color, with beautiful eyes, and smiles, long dark hair, and dark, soft, smooth skin; 
420 is fine, but you don't drink alcohol, or do narcotics. 
you love passionately, and not jealously;
you like to kiss, every part of your lover's body;
you are assertive, not shy, even if you are reserved in your demeanor;
you speak multiple languages;
you prefer to hang out with people from other cultures before criticizing them;
you read poetry aloud, with the sexiest, most seductive voice;
you are 5'8"+ tall;
for you, going to church/temple in your pajamas is fine; and 
you were born on one of the following dates;

